data.name: picboxWarn.ToolTip
data.value: WARNING: This node is operating with a reduced number of connection do due a lack of active IP's. If restarting doesnt fix the problem, please provide more connections by adding IP's through the console or reduce the number of prefered connections.

data.name: lblSync1.ToolTip
data.value: Your computer must be in sync with the rest of the network before you can use most of the features of the program. The synchronization process will happen automatically as long as you are connected to the network.

data.name: txtUnBal.ToolTip
data.value: This is your balance after taking into account unconfirmed transactions to and from your account. When the network next updates, if these transactions get confirmed your balance will be updated. It is advised not to spend unconfirmed transactions.

data.name: txtPriKey.ToolTip
data.value: This is your accounts private key, use the button to the right to hide it from view. Do not let anyone other then you, the account holder gain access to this number. Anyone with this number has access to your account and all funds associated with it.

data.name: txtLogin.ToolTip
data.value: This is your password to your account. Whoever owns this word has access to all funds associasted with the account. This can be hidden from view using the hide button to the right. You cannot change it after it is made but you can create as many accounts as you want and transfer funds between them. Your login word can be as long as you want and contain any unicode characters including spaces. Make sure no one can guess the word or can work it out. If you forget the word and do not have any way to retrive it then your account and all funds associated with it can never be recovered.

data.name: lblOptional.ToolTip
data.value: Transaction fees are sent to those who support the network by running the mining protocal that validates the authenticity of transactions. Transaction fees add an additional insentive for miners to run their mining node. Adding fees is optional but advised to help maintain the integrity of the network. A minimum of 10 is required for all transaction.

data.name: btnNewAdr.ToolTip
data.value: Click to generate a new address linked to your account. For security reasons, it is STRONGLY ADVISED that you use a different address for every transaction to your account. The program will automatically generate new addresses everytime this button is clicked. There is no limit to the number of addresses that can be generated. You must wait at least one second before you can generate a new address.

data.name: txtAdr.ToolTip
data.value: This is an address of your account and is linked to your public key. An address is required by the sender if you wish to receive funds from another account. For security reasons, it is STRONGLY ADVISED that you use a different address for every transaction to your account. For this reason, you cannot store addresses in your address book, only public keys.

data.name: btnStartMine.ToolTip
data.value: Start the mining process. This will begin the task of building blocks and attempting to satisfy the proof-of-work algorithm the program uses to validate transactions. If you complete a block before any other node, you will earn Halfcoins directly to your account. The process is automatic and can be monitored using the console to the right. This process will consume electrical energy and CPU power thus posing a substantial performance decrease to you computer; run at your own risk.

data.name: Label3.ToolTip
data.value: Resets and redownloads the entire blockchain. If this client is producing errors and/or not creating/validating transactions/blocks, this action can fix it. This process will take some time and require connection to the network. The UTXO database will also be updated concurrently.

data.name: lblRebuild.ToolTip
data.value: Rebuilds the entire UTXO database. If this client is producing errors and/or not creating/validating transactions/blocks, this action can fix it. This process will take some time but will not require connection to the network.

data.name: lblRest.ToolTip
data.value: Resets and redownloads the entire blockchain. If this client is producing errors and/or not creating/validating transactions/blocks, this action can fix it. This process will take some time and require connection to the network. The UTXO database will also be updated concurrently.

data.name: cmbNetShip.ToolTip
data.value: If multiple nodes are running under the same NAT, this feature must be enabled. Set one node to be the parent, all others must be set to child. Enter the internal IPv4 of the parent node into the field below on all child nodes.
